7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:32:08+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000\n\n        If you haven’t had an opportunity to review the new edition of the ISO 22000:2018"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"If you haven’t had an opportunity to review the new edition of the ISO 22000:2018 version of the Food Safety Management System (FSMS) Certification standard – the needs for any organization in the organic phenomenon, the update in new standard is that it follows a similar high-level structure (Annex SL) that's typically being employed by all the updated management system ISO standards like ISO 9001, ISO 14001, ISO 27001, and many more. The first and foremost advantage is that currently ISO 22000:2018 has become easier to integrate with different management system standards."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Now that’s the fundamental modification for all the revised standards. In this article, you're about to learn what the ISO 22000:2018 certification standard is regarding, additionally as similarities and variations between it and also the ISO 9001:2015 QMS standard requirements."}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"What is ISO 22000:2018?"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO 22000:2018 is an international standard for Food Safety Management Systems (FSMS) and detailly covers and pinpoints the necessities for any organization in the food chain. And this encompasses organizations that are either directly involved or indirectly comes under the roof of the food chain operations, for instance, feed producers, animal food producers, producers of food ingredients, processors of food items, food makers or retailers, food service suppliers, catering services, food provision center, food storage, instrumentation suppliers for the food business, packaging suppliers for the food business, and producers of animal foods and other food contact materials."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"The recent update to the 2018 version is that the second edition of the ISO 22000 standard, formerly, it absolutely was the ISO 22000:2005 version, that had an extended history of development. Initiated in 1960 from Hazard and Critical Control Points (HACCP) within the food chain system and, later on, food safety system certification (FSSC). It had been established for fulfilling the management system necessities for food safety. So, in 2005, the primary edition of this ISO certification standard was introduced, and therefore the recent version is its second edition."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28"]}],"$L29"]}]}]
