e:[["$","title","0",{"children":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}],["$","meta","1",{"name":"description","content":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000\n\n        If you haven’t had an opportunity to review the new edition of the ISO 22000:2018"}],["$","meta","2",{"name":"keywords","content":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}],["$","meta","3",{"property":"og:title","content":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}],["$","meta","4",{"property":"og:description","content":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000\n\n        If you haven’t had an opportunity to review the new edition of the ISO 22000:2018"}],["$","meta","5",{"property":"og:url","content":"https://wizms.net/relation-and-difference-between-iso-9001-and-iso-22000"}],["$","meta","6",{"property":"og:type","content":"article"}],["$","meta","7",{"property":"article:published_time","content":"2026-01-02T06:32:08+00:00"}],["$","meta","8",{"name":"twitter:card","content":"summary"}],["$","meta","9",{"name":"twitter:title","content":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}],["$","meta","10",{"name":"twitter:description","content":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000\n\n        If you haven’t had an opportunity to review the new edition of the ISO 22000:2018"}],["$","link","11",{"rel":"icon","href":"/favicon.ico"}],["$","$L2a","12",{}]]
10:["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"This ISO certification standard for food safety provides strategic direction for a company to enhance its overall food safety performance on the basis of certain process approach and specific FSMS necessities within the standard. By implementing a FSMS on the basis of ISO 22000, a company or organization will profit in the following areas:"}]
11:["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Its ability to produce safe food product and services while systematically meeting client and applicable compliance obligations (also termed “legal and statutory requirements”)"}]
12:["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Its ability to exhibit compliance with FSMS requirements"}]
13:["$","p","9",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Identification of problems concerning food safety, addressing risks related to its food safety system"}]
14:["$","p","10",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"What are the biggest variations and modification made in ISO 22000:2018 edition?"}]
15:["$","p","11",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"While it contains all of identical needs for Quality Management Systems because the other revised standards, there are some specific technical necessities that create this ISO standard explicit for organizations in the food industry. Clause 8 of this ISO certification standard specifies those necessities, that essentially make sure that the food safety on a technical level. Those necessities are:"}]
16:["$","p","12",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Operational designing & management – how the organization plans its operations (processing) and at the same time controls for food safety"}]
17:["$","p","13",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Prerequisites programs (PRPs) – identification of basic conditions and activities that are necessary to take care of a hygienical setting throughout the food chain"}]
18:["$","p","14",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Traceability system – a system to trace the food product uniquely"}]
19:["$","p","15",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Emergency readiness & control – identification of all the doable emergency situations and arrangements to manage them"}]
1a:["$","p","16",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Hazard control – this includes performance of hazard analysis, definition and validation of management measures, preparation of HACCP (hazard and critical control points) and/or OPRP (operational prerequisites programs) plans."}]
1b:["$","p","17",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Updating information – to update the data regarding PRPs and to keep the hazard management plans updated"}]
1c:["$","p","18",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Control of observance and measurement – how the organization is controlling its monitoring and measuring systems"}]
1d:["$","p","19",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Verification concerning PRPs and hazard control plans – how the PRPs and hazard control plans are verified and analyzed"}]
1e:["$","p","20",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Control of nonconforming product and processes– how the organization controls its nonconforming product and processes, as well as the factors for recall or withdrawal"}]
1f:["$","p","21",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"These necessities are obvious and provides very comprehensive details concerning how you would like to manage and guarantee your food safety."}]
20:["$","p","22",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"What are the variations and similarities between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000:2018?"}]
21:["$","p","23",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Since each standards were revised supported the new high-level structure (Annex SL), it's become easier to seek out the similarities and variations between the standards. Each and every standards have ten clauses with a similar main titles. So, if we tend to see the clauses demonstrating the necessities of context of the organization, leadership, planning, support, performance analysis, and enhancements – typically, they're all the same. The major distinction between the standards is in clause 8. inquiring the technical needs of clause 8, we tend to see that in ISO 22000, clause 8 give a basic framework to make sure food safety in the entire food chain operations, whereas in ISO 9001, clause 8 provides a generic framework to make sure quality of processes (and those are general and might be applied to any organization of any scope)."}]
22:["$","p","24",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Let’s have a quick check up on a similar needs if you're planning to implement both standards:"}]
23:["$","p","25",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Context of the organization (internal & external problems, interested parties, scope)"}]
24:["$","p","26",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Control of documented data (documents & records control)"}]
25:["$","p","27",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Addressing risks & opportunities, coming up with & objectives"}]
26:["$","p","28",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Improvement, corrective actions"}]
27:["$","p","29",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Management review & internal audits"}]
28:["$","p","30",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Competence, communication, coaching & awareness"}]
29:["$","footer",null,{"className":"mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-600 bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded","children":"Relation and difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000"}]]}]}]
